1️⃣ From libraries / standard headers
From ncurses (#include <ncurses.h>)

Types

WINDOW — opaque window struct

KEY_UP, KEY_DOWN — special key codes

A_REVERSE — attribute for reverse video

Functions

initscr() — initialize ncurses

noecho() — don’t echo typed characters

cbreak() — disable line buffering, so keys are sent immeadiately to program

newwin() — create a new window

keypad() — enable function keys / arrows

box() — draw a border around a window

wattron() — turn on an attribute in a window

wattroff() — turn off an attribute in a window

mvwprintw() — move cursor + print formatted text in a window

wgetch() — get character input from a window

mvprintw() — move cursor + print formatted text on stdscr

printw() — print formatted text on stdscr

clrtoeol() — clear from cursor to end of line

refresh() — refresh stdscr

getch() — get a key from stdscr

echo() / noecho() — turn on/off input echoing

endwin() — exit ncurses mode

getnstr() - Reads a string from the user via the terminal up to n characters

From standard C (#include <stdio.h>, <stdlib.h>, <string.h>)

printf family is indirectly used (mvprintw, printw, scanw, getnstr internally call them)

scanf family used via scanw

char, int, float — built-in types

sizeof — operator used for arrays (if used)

2️⃣ From your own code / student.h
Functions

loadFromCSV()

saveToCSV()

addStudent(char *name, float grade)

listStudents()

deleteStudent(int id)

editStudent(int id, char *name, float grade)

sortByName()

sortByGrade()

exportToJSON()

drawMenu(WINDOW *win, int highlight) — you defined this yourself

Variables (local / program-defined)

In drawMenu

choices — array of menu strings

n — number of menu items

i — loop counter

highlight — parameter

In main

startx, starty — window position

width, height — window size

menuwin — pointer to WINDOW

choice — selected menu option

highlight — currently highlighted menu item

name, grade — used when adding/editing a student

id — student ID for delete/edit

✅ Notes / tips

Anything starting with mvwprintw, wgetch, keypad, box, wattron, wattroff, mvprintw, etc. is ncurses.

Anything related to students (addStudent, editStudent, listStudents, etc.) is your own code.

Local variables inside your functions (i, choice, highlight, name, grade) are also yours.
